cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the capacity of wireless networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the throughput efficiency of CSMA scheduling, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper explores the capacity of CSMA networks, which are distributed and random, and compares it to centralized TDMA networks. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper studies the scalability of CSMA networks, which is relevant to social and information networks. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper addresses implementation issues of the proposed CSMA scheme, which is related to performance.
